data.name: label2.Text
data.value: The objective of the game is to direct the falling blocks into different positions as they land. A row can be cleared by filling an entire row with blocks. Clearing more rows will increase the level (Causing the blocks to fall faster) and also increase the score. The score is increased by a larger amount if more rows are cleared at once. The main objective of the game is to earn the highest possible score.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: After you have added your score, You can click either of the two navigation buttons on the screen to either play the game again or return to the main menu. If you wish to clear the scores, click the “High Scores” menu strip item and then click the “Clear High Scores” Item.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: Once you finish a game you will be shown the high score board along with your score. You can enter your name or nickname in the text box and the score will be added to the high score board when you click the “Add Score” button.

data.name: label15.Text
data.value:
Q) Can I rotate a block counter-clockwise? A) No, Blocks can only be rotated clockwise.
Q) Can I start at a specific level? A) No, every player will always start at level 1.
Q) What if I don’t enter a name at the high score screen? A) A score will still be added but it will use the name “Unknown”
Q) Can I use the mouse to play? A) No, the game requires the use of the keyboard.
Q) Is there a most common/most rare piece in this game? A) No, Each block has an equal probability of appearing. However, you’ll never get the same block twice in a row.
Q) Can I see the scores past the top 10? A) No, The top 10 score are the only scores that can be viewed.
